This will show the Create Product endpoint with the request body and response definitions.




Q- How to set up a project in FastAPI for CRUD operations?
A clean way to set up a FastAPI CRUD project is to separate your application into modules for routes, models, schemas, database configuration, and CRUD logic.
📁 Project Folder Hierarchy
fastapi-crud/
│── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── main.py
│   ├── database.py
│   ├── models.py
│   ├── schemas.py
│   ├── crud.py
│   ├── routes.py
│   └── config.py
│
├── requirements.txt
├── .env
└── venv/


Step 1: Create Virtual Environment
Command 1-> python -m venv venv
Command 2-> venv\Scripts\activate

Step 2: Install Dependencies
Command 3-> pip install fastapi uvicorn sqlalchemy pydantic python-dotenv
Save dependencies:
Command 4-> pip freeze > requirements.txt

Step 3: Database Configuration
Now create folders 
First folder -> fastapi-crud 
Now under fastapi-crud create app folder

Now create files (under app folder ) :-
database.py
from sqlalchemy import create_engine
from sqlalchemy.orm import declarative_base, sessionmaker

DATABASE_URL = "sqlite:///./test.db"

engine = create_engine(
    DATABASE_URL,
    connect_args={"check_same_thread": False}
)

SessionLocal = sessionmaker(
    autocommit=False,
    autoflush=False,
    bind=engine
)

Base = declarative_base()


def get_db():
    db = SessionLocal()
    try:
        yield db
    finally:
        db.close()


Step 4: Create Model
models.py
from sqlalchemy import Column, Integer, String
from .database import Base


class User(Base):
    __tablename__ = "users"

    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True, index=True)
